OL,3,CFamilies of Nottingham attack victims
OL,4,Cwelcome decision to review homicide law
OL,6,FThe families of three people killed in
OL,7,Fthe Nottingham attacks have welcomed
OL,8,Fthe decision to review homicide law.
OL,10,FBarnaby Webber, 19, Grace O'Malley-
OL,11,FKumar, 19, and Ian Coates, 65, were
OL,12,Fstabbed to death by Valdo Calocane in
OL,13,FNottingham in June 2022.
OL,15,FCalocane, who had been diagnosed with
OL,16,Fparanoid schizophrenia, was given a
OL,17,Fhospital order for manslaughter on the
OL,18,Fbasis of diminished responsibility in
OL,19,FJanuary.
