OL,3,CFamilies of Nottingham attack victims
OL,4,Cwelcome decision to review homicide law
OL,6,FPublished in 2006, the report called
OL,7,Fon the government to consider changing
OL,8,Fhomicide, currently categorised by two
OL,9,Ftiers of murder and manslaughter, into
OL,10,Fthree tiers - first degree murder,
OL,11,Fsecond degree murder and manslaughter.
OL,13,FIn a letter to the families, Alex
OL,14,FDavies-Jones MP, the minister for
OL,15,Fvictims and violence against women and
OL,16,Fgirls, said the review would also
OL,17,Fconsider issues raised by the HM Crown
OL,18,FProsecution Service Inspectorate
OL,19,F(HMCPSI), which looked into how the
OL,20,FCrown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,21,Fhandled the case.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
